Module org.nasdanika.graph
Package org.nasdanika.graph.processor.emf

Class AbstractEObjectFactory<T extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject,P extends SemanticProcessor<T>>

java.lang.Object
org.nasdanika.graph.processor.emf.AbstractEObjectFactory<T,P>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Composeable<ProcessorFactory<P,ProcessorInfo<P>,ProcessorInfo<P>>>, NopEndpointProcessorFactory<P,ProcessorInfo<P>>, ProcessorFactory<P,ProcessorInfo<P>,ProcessorInfo<P>>
Direct Known Subclasses:
PropertySourceEObjectFactory
public abstract class AbstractEObjectFactory<T extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject,P extends SemanticProcessor<T>> extends Object implements NopEndpointProcessorFactory<P,ProcessorInfo<P>>
Creates EObjects from graph elements and wires them together using diagram element properties. Uses ProcessorInfo as handler and enpoint type.
Author:
Pavel

    • setParent

      protected void setParent(ProcessorConfig<P> config, P processor, ProcessorInfo<P> parentProcessorInfo, ProgressMonitor progressMonitor, Consumer<Throwable> failureConsumer)
      Sets parent. If parent is null this method sets itself to be called for the grand parent etc. If child reference property is not null then the semantic element is injected into the parent's references specified in the child reference property. Otherwise, if parent reference property is not null then the parent is injected into the semantic element's reference specified in the parent reference property.
      Parameters:
      semanticElement -
      parentProcessorInfo -

    • setParent

      public void setParent(T child, T parent, ProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
      This method calls protected setParent() method to establish parent/child relationships between semantic elements using data from the graph elements from which these semantic elements were created. This method uses ProcessorConfigAdapters to retrieve graph configs to pass to setParent()
